---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { withBase } from '../lib/paths';
---
<style>
.persona-hero { padding: 72px 0 64px; position: relative; overflow: hidden; }
.persona-hero-ic { background: linear-gradient(160deg, #EFF6FF 0%, #DBEAFE 100%); }
.persona-hero h1 { color: var(--primary); font-size: clamp(28px, 3.5vw, 44px); font-weight: 900; letter-spacing: -0.03em; line-height: 1.1; margin-bottom: 16px; }
.persona-hero p { font-size: 18px; color: var(--gray-700); line-height: 1.6; max-width: 600px; margin-bottom: 28px; }
.persona-nav {
  background: var(--white);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-100);
  position: sticky;
  top: 64px;
  z-index: 90;
}
.persona-nav-inner {
  max-width: 1160px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 0 24px;
  display: flex;
  gap: 4px;
  height: 52px;
  align-items: center;
}
.persona-nav-inner a {
  font-size: 14px;
  font-weight: 500;
  color: var(--gray-500);
  text-decoration: none;
  padding: 6px 14px;
  border-radius: 7px;
  transition: background 0.15s, color 0.15s;
}
.persona-nav-inner a:hover { background: var(--gray-50); color: var(--primary); }
.use-case-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
  gap: 20px;
  margin-top: 40px;
}
.use-case-card { background: var(--white); border-radius: 14px; padding: 24px; border: 1px solid var(--gray-100); }
.use-case-card .icon { font-size: 24px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
.use-case-card h4 { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 8px; }
.use-case-card p { font-size: 13px; color: var(--gray-500); line-height: 1.6; }
.persona-section { padding: 80px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-100); }
.persona-section:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
.quote-block { background: var(--gray-50); border-radius: 14px; padding: 28px; border-left: 4px solid var(--secondary); margin: 32px 0; }
.quote-block p { font-size: 17px; font-style: italic; color: var(--gray-700); line-height: 1.65; margin-bottom: 12px; }
.quote-block .attribution { font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--primary); }
.quote-block .role { font-size: 12px; color: var(--gray-500); margin-top: 2px; }
@media (max-width: 768px) { .use-case-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
</style>

<BaseLayout title="Solutions — Cadence for Every Layer of the Org" description="Cadence works for ICs who want visibility, managers who want to be better, senior leaders who need signal across their chain, and CHROs who need operational command." activeNav="solutions">

<div class="page-hero">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="breadcrumb"><a href={withBase('/')}>Home</a><span>/</span>Solutions</div>
    <div class="section-badge" style="background:rgba(245,166,35,0.15);border:1px solid rgba(245,166,35,0.25);color:var(--accent-light);">Built for every layer</div>
    <h1>One platform. <span class="accent">Four perspectives.</span></h1>
    <p>Cadence looks different depending on where you sit. The IC sees their career path and coaching. The manager sees their team health and 1:1 workspace. The CHRO sees the whole organization — in one view. Same platform, different lenses.</p>
    <div class="btn-group" style="justify-content:center;">
      <a href="#individual-contributors" class="btn btn-white btn-lg">Find your role ↓</a>
      <a href={withBase('/beta')} class="btn btn-white-outline btn-lg">Request access</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="persona-nav">
  <div class="persona-nav-inner">
    <a href="#individual-contributors">👤 Individual Contributors</a>
    <a href="#managers">🧑‍💼 Managers</a>
    <a href="#senior-leaders">📡 Senior Leaders</a>
    <a href="#chro">🏛️ CHROs</a>
  </div>
</div>

<section class="persona-section" id="individual-contributors">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="feature-block">
      <div>
        <div class="section-badge">Individual Contributors</div>
        <h2 class="section-headline">Finally know where you stand — and where you're going.</h2>
        <p class="section-subhead" style="max-width:540px;margin-bottom:24px;">Management quality varies wildly across organizations. Some ICs get a manager who coaches them, advocates for them, and develops them deliberately. Most get someone who is too busy, too inconsistent, or too conflict-averse to be honest.</p>
        <p style="font-size:16px;color:var(--gray-500);line-height:1.75;margin-bottom:24px;">Cadence doesn't fix your manager — it creates a system where good management happens by default, not by luck. Your goals are visible. Your 1:1s are documented. Your feedback is captured. Your career path is explicit.</p>
        <div class="quote-block">
          <p>"I spent 18 months at my last company not knowing if I was on track for a promotion or heading toward a PIP. Nobody told me. There was no system. Cadence changes that — everything is visible."</p>
          <div class="attribution">Software Engineer, L3</div>
          <div class="role">Beta program participant</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="use-case-grid" style="grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;">
          <div class="use-case-card"><div class="icon">📋</div><h4>Your 1:1 record</h4><p>Every 1:1 you've ever had with your manager — documented, searchable, private.</p></div>
          <div class="use-case-card"><div class="icon">🎯</div><h4>Your goals</h4><p>See your goals and their status in real time. Surfaces in every 1:1 so they stay active.</p></div>
          <div class="use-case-card"><div class="icon">✦</div><h4>AI coaching, just for you</h4><p>After every 1:1, you get private coaching on the conversation — separate from what your manager receives.</p></div>
          <div class="use-case-card"><div class="icon">🏗️</div><h4>Your career path</h4><p>Your role definition and growth path are always visible. You know exactly what's expected at your level.</p></div>
          <div class="use-case-card"><div class="icon">⭐</div><h4>Recognition</h4><p>Give and receive recognition tied to values. Your recognition history follows your tenure.</p></div>
          <div class="use-case-card"><div class="icon">🗳️</div><h4>Your voice</h4><p>Pulse and engagement surveys designed for anonymous honesty.</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="persona-section" id="managers" style="background:var(--gray-50);">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="feature-block reverse">
      <div>
        <div class="section-badge">Managers</div>
        <h2 class="section-headline">The workspace you actually run your team in.</h2>
        <p style="font-size:16px;color:var(--gray-500);line-height:1.75;margin-bottom:20px;">Good management is hard. It requires you to be consistent, observant, coaching-oriented, and data-informed — all while doing your actual job. Most managers fail not because they don't care, but because they have no system.</p>
        <p style="font-size:16px;color:var(--gray-500);line-height:1.75;margin-bottom:24px;">Cadence is the system. Run your 1:1s here. Track your goals here. Know who you're over-correcting and under-recognizing before it becomes a problem. 9-box calibration remains a roadmap preview.</p>
        <div class="quote-block">
          <p>"I've been a manager for six years. I thought I was good at it. The first month with Cadence showed me three relationships I was managing on autopilot that needed real attention."</p>
          <div class="attribution">VP Engineering</div>
          <div class="role">Beta program participant</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="use-case-grid" style="grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;">
          <div class="use-case-card"><div class="icon">💬</div><h4>1:1 workspace</h4><p>Structured agendas, shared with your direct report. Both parties contribute topics.</p></div>
          <div class="use-case-card"><div class="icon">✦</div><h4>Post-meeting AI coaching</h4><p>After every 1:1, private coaching: what you said well, what you could have handled differently.</p></div>
          <div class="use-case-card"><div class="icon">⬛</div><h4>9-box guidance roadmap</h4><p>Calibration guidance is planned, not part of current beta access.</p></div>
          <div class="use-case-card"><div class="icon">⭐</div><h4>Recognition tracking</h4><p>Your 5:1 ratio — real time, tracked, and visible to your manager.</p></div>
          <div class="use-case-card"><div class="icon">🎯</div><h4>Team goals</h4><p>See every direct report's goal status at a glance. Surface blockers in 1:1s.</p></div>
          <div class="use-case-card"><div class="icon">📊</div><h4>Team health signal</h4><p>Aggregated survey results with team-level attribution.</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="persona-section" id="senior-leaders">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="feature-block">
      <div>
        <div class="section-badge">Senior Leaders (L2+)</div>
        <h2 class="section-headline">Complete signal across your entire management chain.</h2>
        <p style="font-size:16px;color:var(--gray-500);line-height:1.75;margin-bottom:20px;">Senior leaders are accountable for outcomes produced by people they don't directly manage. They need signal without micromanagement — the ability to see what's happening across their chain without having to ask or infer.</p>
        <div class="quote-block">
          <p>"I used to find out about management problems through resignations and complaints. Now I find out 90 days earlier, when the data starts showing the pattern."</p>
          <div class="attribution">Chief Product Officer</div>
          <div class="role">Beta program participant</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="use-case-grid" style="grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;">
          <div class="use-case-card"><div class="icon">📡</div><h4>Chain-of-command view</h4><p>See every manager in your org: 1:1 compliance, recognition ratio, ER activity, effectiveness composite.</p></div>
          <div class="use-case-card"><div class="icon">⚠️</div><h4>Manager signal review</h4><p>Cadence helps leaders review manager activity across 1:1s, goals, recognition, and ER context without implying predictive attrition.</p></div>
          <div class="use-case-card"><div class="icon">⬛</div><h4>Calibration participation roadmap</h4><p>Independent 9-box ratings and convergence views are planned roadmap capabilities.</p></div>
          <div class="use-case-card"><div class="icon">🏆</div><h4>Top talent visibility roadmap</h4><p>Key Value Driver and retention-risk views are planned roadmap capabilities, not current beta access.</p></div>
          <div class="use-case-card"><div class="icon">📊</div><h4>Survey signal aggregated</h4><p>Engagement and pulse results broken down by manager.</p></div>
          <div class="use-case-card"><div class="icon">📈</div><h4>Goal health across teams</h4><p>See the goal status for all teams in your chain. Identify blockers sitting unresolved.</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="persona-section" id="chro" style="background:var(--primary);">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="feature-block" style="border-bottom:none;">
      <div>
        <div class="section-badge" style="background:rgba(245,166,35,0.15);color:var(--accent-light);">CHROs &amp; People Leaders</div>
        <h2 class="section-headline white">Operational command — not just reporting.</h2>
        <p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.75);font-size:16px;line-height:1.75;margin-bottom:20px;">The CHRO's traditional view is backwards-looking: turnover reports, ER case counts, survey summaries published weeks after they're conducted. It tells you what happened, not what's happening.</p>
        <p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.75);font-size:16px;line-height:1.75;margin-bottom:24px;">Cadence gives the CHRO an operational command center — real-time visibility into the management activity driving the outcomes they're responsible for.</p>
        <div class="quote-block" style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.06);border-left-color:var(--accent);">
          <p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.85);">"The ROI conversation starts with replacing fragmented management workflows. Roadmap previews show where Cadence is going next."</p>
          <div class="attribution" style="color:white;">CHRO, Mid-market technology company</div>
          <div class="role" style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.5);">Beta program participant · 850 employees</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="use-case-grid" style="grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;">
          <div class="use-case-card" style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.07);border-color:rgba(255,255,255,0.12);"><div class="icon">🏆</div><h4 style="color:white;">Culture Scorecard</h4><p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.65);">Composite org health score connecting every signal source. Board-ready reporting.</p></div>
          <div class="use-case-card" style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.07);border-color:rgba(255,255,255,0.12);"><div class="icon">📋</div><h4 style="color:white;">ER pipeline</h4><p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.65);">All active cases, PIPs, and formal investigations in one view.</p></div>
          <div class="use-case-card" style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.07);border-color:rgba(255,255,255,0.12);"><div class="icon">⬛</div><h4 style="color:white;">Calibration command roadmap</h4><p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.65);">9-box cycle progress, KVD nominations, and intervention workflows are roadmap previews.</p></div>
          <div class="use-case-card" style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.07);border-color:rgba(255,255,255,0.12);"><div class="icon">📉</div><h4 style="color:white;">Retention-risk roadmap</h4><p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.65);">Predictive retention warnings are planned, not currently available in production.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div style="text-align:center;margin-top:32px;">
          <a href={withBase('/beta')} class="btn btn-accent btn-lg">Request a CHRO walkthrough →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section-cta">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Ready to see it in action?</h2>
    <p>Beta access is by invitation. Tell us about your org and we'll walk you through the experience built for your role.</p>
    <div class="btn-group" style="justify-content:center;">
      <a href={withBase('/beta')} class="btn btn-white btn-lg">Request beta access</a>
      <a href={withBase('/product')} class="btn btn-white-outline btn-lg">Explore the platform</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

</BaseLayout>
